<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="2" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,1261,1646]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,352,1405,1430]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Distribution.</emphasis>
Throughout Europe (excluding 
<collectingCountry box="[740,894,1405,1430]" name="United Kingdom" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Great Britain</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[962,1046,1405,1430]" name="Ireland" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Ireland</collectingCountry>
), 
<collectingCountry box="[1071,1120,1406,1429]" name="Iran" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Iran</collectingCountry>
: Gorgan, Hesarchal valley (Sardab valley), Mirabi Mt., and Nesa (Lederer 1871; 
<bibRefCitation box="[758,933,1441,1466]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" refId="ref19875" refString="Osthelder, L. (1938) Neue Kleinfalter aus dem Tahte Soleiman in Nord-Persien. (Lep.). Mitteilungen der Munchener Entomologischen Gesellschaft, 28 (1), 17 - 29." type="journal article">Osthelder 1938</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation box="[945,1056,1441,1466]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" refId="ref20104" refString="Toll, S. (1948) Beitrag zur Mikrolepidopterenfauna von Nordost-Persien. Zeitschrift der Wiener entomologischen Gesellschaft, 32 (1947), 107 - 116, pls. 4 - 6." type="journal article">Toll 1948</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation box="[1067,1206,1441,1466]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" refId="ref19135" refString="Amsel, H. G. (1961) Die Microlepidopteren der Brandt'schen Iran-Ausbeute. 5. Teil. Arkiv for Zoologie (N. S.), Stockholm (ser. 2) 13 (17), 323 - 445, pls. 1 - 9." type="journal article">Amsel 1961</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation box="[1218,1362,1441,1466]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" refId="ref19338" refString="Goater, B. (2005) Evergestinae. In: Goater, B., Nuss, M. &amp; W. Speidel, Pyraloidea I. In: P. Huemer &amp; O. Karsholt, Microlepidoptera of Europe 4. Apollo Books, Stenstrup, pp. 69 - 107, 182 - 183, 190 - 193, 208 - 223, 244 - 256." type="book chapter">Goater 2005</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="2" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,1261,1646]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1477,1502]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Remarks.</emphasis>
Two of the three subspecies of this species viz., 
<taxonomicName authority="Osthelder, 1938" authorityName="Osthelder" authorityYear="1938" box="[889,1352,1477,1502]" class="Insecta" family="Crambidae" genus="Evergestis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="aenealis" subSpecies="dimorphalis">
<emphasis box="[889,1161,1477,1501]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">E. aenealis dimorphalis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation box="[1171,1352,1477,1502]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" refId="ref19875" refString="Osthelder, L. (1938) Neue Kleinfalter aus dem Tahte Soleiman in Nord-Persien. (Lep.). Mitteilungen der Munchener Entomologischen Gesellschaft, 28 (1), 17 - 29." type="journal article">Osthelder, 1938</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Toll, 1948" authorityName="Toll" authorityYear="1948" class="Insecta" family="Crambidae" genus="Evergestis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="aenealis" subSpecies="obscura">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">E. aenealis obscura</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation box="[352,472,1513,1538]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" refId="ref20104" refString="Toll, S. (1948) Beitrag zur Mikrolepidopterenfauna von Nordost-Persien. Zeitschrift der Wiener entomologischen Gesellschaft, 32 (1947), 107 - 116, pls. 4 - 6." type="journal article">Toll, 1948</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, have been described from 
<collectingCountry box="[788,833,1514,1537]" name="Iran" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Iran</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation box="[850,1029,1513,1538]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" refId="ref19875" refString="Osthelder, L. (1938) Neue Kleinfalter aus dem Tahte Soleiman in Nord-Persien. (Lep.). Mitteilungen der Munchener Entomologischen Gesellschaft, 28 (1), 17 - 29." type="journal article">Osthelder 1938</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation box="[1042,1155,1513,1538]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" refId="ref20104" refString="Toll, S. (1948) Beitrag zur Mikrolepidopterenfauna von Nordost-Persien. Zeitschrift der Wiener entomologischen Gesellschaft, 32 (1947), 107 - 116, pls. 4 - 6." type="journal article">Toll 1948</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation box="[1169,1315,1513,1538]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" refId="ref19338" refString="Goater, B. (2005) Evergestinae. In: Goater, B., Nuss, M. &amp; W. Speidel, Pyraloidea I. In: P. Huemer &amp; O. Karsholt, Microlepidoptera of Europe 4. Apollo Books, Stenstrup, pp. 69 - 107, 182 - 183, 190 - 193, 208 - 223, 244 - 256." type="book chapter">Goater 2005</bibRefCitation>
). The 
<typeStatus box="[1388,1436,1514,1538]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">type</typeStatus>
localities of the former and latter subspecies are Hesarchal, Sardab valley in 
<collectingRegion box="[1049,1124,1549,1574]" country="Iran" name="Alborz" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Elburz</collectingRegion>
area (
<bibRefCitation box="[1199,1377,1549,1574]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" refId="ref19875" refString="Osthelder, L. (1938) Neue Kleinfalter aus dem Tahte Soleiman in Nord-Persien. (Lep.). Mitteilungen der Munchener Entomologischen Gesellschaft, 28 (1), 17 - 29." type="journal article">Osthelder 1938</bibRefCitation>
) and Mirabi Mt. in NE 
<collectingCountry box="[362,407,1586,1609]" name="Iran" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Iran</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation box="[424,538,1585,1610]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" refId="ref20104" refString="Toll, S. (1948) Beitrag zur Mikrolepidopterenfauna von Nordost-Persien. Zeitschrift der Wiener entomologischen Gesellschaft, 32 (1947), 107 - 116, pls. 4 - 6." type="journal article">Toll 1948</bibRefCitation>
), respectively. The examined specimens have a gray forewing with yellowishbrown tint that match with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Osthelder" authorityYear="1938" box="[455,721,1621,1645]" class="Insecta" family="Crambidae" genus="Evergestis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="aenealis" subSpecies="dimorphalis">
<emphasis box="[455,721,1621,1645]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">E. aenealis dimorphalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
